article.headline: St. Francis (NY) 76, Wagner 75
article.story: NEW YORK -- Dre Calloway made a layup with 2.8 seconds remaining to lift St. Francis Brooklyn to a 76-75 win over Wagner on Thursday night in Northeast Conference action. There were 19 lead changes and 10 ties, including 73-73 with 2:20 left. After Lowell Ulmer made the second of two free throws to push the Terriers (11-15, 7-8) in front, Latif Rivers' jumper gave the Seahawks a 75-74 lead with 1:33 left. Although Jalen Cannon missed a layup for St. Francis Brooklyn, the Terriers got another chance when Wagner turned the ball over. Following Calloway's basket, Rivers missed a 3-point attempt at the buzzer. Ben Mockford's 18 points led St. Francis Brooklyn, which also beat the Seahawks 71-52 on Jan. 12. Travis Nichols added 16 points, Cannon 13 and Calloway 11. Jonathon Williams scored 16 points to lead Wagner (15-11, 9-6), which came in having won three of its past four games.
